<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5448: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-21"><hi rend="italic">October 21,
                                1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received October 22, 10:55
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[From <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>:]</p>
                        <p>442. October 21st, 10 a.m. Referring to Department’s October 16th, 5 p.m.
                            Omsk Government does not consider incident in question is yet closed.
                            Every effort will be made to investigate this matter and punish those
                            guilty of the outrage. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>